          <dt>Problem</dt>
          <dd>Recruiters and applicants need one place to manage job listings and applications — with different capabilities for each role and secure access to sensitive data.</dd>
        </div>
        <div>
          <dt>What I did</dt>
          <dd>
            <ul>
              <li>Built a full-stack job portal with Spring Boot, Thymeleaf, Spring Security, and JPA.</li>
              <li>Recruiters can create job listings and view applicants; applicants can apply for open positions and track their applications.</li>
              <li>Implemented secure user authentication and role-based access control.</li>
              <li>Dynamic content rendering with Thymeleaf; persistent storage with Spring Data JPA and MySQL.</li>
            </ul>
          </dd>
